english:
{GREEK}
...I see.
South of here is no longer the
realm of men. Stay sharp.\p {GREEK}
Take this as a parting gift.
Please accept it.

{GREEK}
{...}..Mm.
{...}..I see... mm-hm..{...}.{...}
Just as I thought.
...Understood.\p{GREEK}
{...}{WARRICK}.
{VOGEL} is calling for you.

{WARRICK}
The whole ceiling is a mural.
{REINA}
The tale of the {DEMON GOD} and the
DIVINE DRAGONs, 900 years past.

{VOGEL}
...So you've come.
I am {VOGEL}, the {PRIEST DRAGON} who
rules this land.\p {VOGEL}
You seek where {PADDISH} dwells.\p {VOGEL}
South.
Head south.\p {VOGEL}
If you would meet {PADDISH}, make
for the {FRODITE FOREST}.\p {VOGEL}
The {KNIFE} will guide you from there.

{VOGEL}
But Lord {MEPHIS} now lies in a
long slumber within the seal.\p {VOGEL}
And that golden {KNIFE} is the very
key to free the sealed Lord {MEPHIS}.\p {WARRICK}
...Sealed?
Why would such a thing happen?\p {VOGEL}
.{...}..{...}..

{VOGEL}
The monsters of {KULEIA} have moved
to invade {SERUSH}.\p {VOGEL}
Lord {MEPHIS} must be revived before
it is too late.\p {VOGEL}
Deliver that {KNIFE} to {PADDISH} with
all haste.\p {VOGEL}
And revive Lord {MEPHIS}.\p {VOGEL}
South.
Head south, {WARRICK}.

{COUNT CAL}
You know the legend of the {DEMON GOD}
and the two Divine DRAGONs.
p
{COUNT CAL}
In most tellings they are called
demon dragons, not Divine DRAGONs.
Those two were dragons of the
divine realm.

{COUNT CAL}
And aiding the Priest DRAGONs are
the GUARDIANs.
p
{COUNT CAL}
A {GUARDIAN} serves as the Priest
DRAGON's hands, carrying the will
of the land to the world.
p
{COUNT CAL}
One {GUARDIAN} is chosen per Priest
DRAGON, and given {GUARDIAN} {ARMOR}
as the proof of it.

{COUNT CAL}
This castle was once the home of
the {PRIEST DRAGON}, the {FIRE DRAGON}
{BREI}. ...Until that day.

{COUNT CAL}
With {PRIEST DRAGON} {BREI} dead, the
{SPIRITS} of this land grew wild
once more.
{COUNT CAL}
A century on, it became a {SAND SEA}
where no {SPIRIT} dwells.
{COUNT CAL}
At {PADDISH}'s behest, I govern
this land in his stead.
{COUNT CAL}
Yet even with my power as a
vampire lord, I can barely hold
things as they are.
...A sorry tale, is it not.

Take this key.
It opens the door to the labyrinth.\p{CLAYBOURNE}
The labyrinth leads to {FRODITE FOREST}
.
The dragon should be at the temple
deep within the woods.

So this is the 'errand' {COUNT CAL}
mentioned.
{FURNIS}
Still, that's a mean trick.
If you knew {MARGIS}, you could've
just said so.

{SAND CASTLE} was built to honor the
{PRIEST DRAGON}. With the {FIRE DRAGON}
gone, {COUNT CAL} governs the {SPIRITS}
of that region now.
\p{SETH}
We guardian knights owe {COUNT CAL}
a tremendous debt. Even now he
advises us on all sorts of things.
\p{SETH}
...Still, I'm relieved. You're just
the people {BLAFORD} said you'd be.
\p{SETH}
He talks about you so happily.

A friend... You mean {LAMBERT}.
He was a brave man.\p{SETH}
Ask {PADDISH} about the knives
yourself.
...You'll be more at peace that way.\p{SETH}
Come, let's go.

{WHITE DRAGON} {PADDISH}
A {GUARDIAN} of the {DIVINE DRAGON}
-- such a thing has never been.
Go with great care.

{WHITE DRAGON} {PADDISH}
In truth, the {GUARDIAN} of the
{DIVINE DRAGON} was but a title.
Never before has a {DIVINE DRAGON}
made a {GUARDIAN}.\p {WHITE DRAGON} {PADDISH}
What power that armor holds, I
cannot begin to imagine. Whether
a human can ever wear it.{...}

White Dragon {PADDISH}
...So you are {BLAFORD}'s sister.
Fear not. Right now {BLAFORD} has
gone to the {SAND CASTLE}.\pWhite Dragon {PADDISH}
{KULEIA} is a moving city that
stays in no one place. At last we
learned it shifts in a 3-year cycle.\pWhite Dragon {PADDISH}
But a powerful barrier surrounds
it. To break through, we will need
's aid.

White Dragon {PADDISH}
If the magic succeeded, {BLAFORD}
should already be inside as a scout.\pWhite Dragon {PADDISH}
Our strength is far from enough,
yet we must strike before the
demon god moves in earnest.

White Dragon {PADDISH}
...You will go, then.
I entrust Lady {ASTARTE} to you,
{WARRICK}. You alone are our hope.\pWhite Dragon {PADDISH}
{SETH}.
Lead them all.

White Dragon {PADDISH}
I see... then you do not know
the power of this seal either.\p White Dragon {PADDISH}
Two Divine Dragons... {GOLD DRAGON}
{MEPHIS}, and {SILVER DRAGON} {ASTARTE}.
The forebears of us Priest Dragons.\p White Dragon {PADDISH}
900 years ago they destroyed the
{DEMON GOD} utterly from this world.
...But it was won by mutual ruin.

{WHITE DRAGON} {PADDISH}
{KULEIA} is shielded by a powerful
barrier to keep out intruders.
It is hard work, but {BLAFORD}
will find a way through.

{MEPHIS}
{ASTARTE} has fully revived, but my
own revival will take centuries.
\p{MEPHIS}
The {PRIEST DRAGON} cannot stop
{ASTARTE}.
...Nor can the {GUARDIAN}.
\p{MEPHIS}
Yet one other can stand against
{ASTARTE} besides me.

{MEPHIS}
The {GOLDEN KNIFE} you held
split my soul into three.
\p{MEPHIS}
I journeyed with you, always
watching over you.
\p{MEPHIS}
And {WARRICK}, though you have
a human softness, your gift
as a guardian is plain.
\p{MEPHIS}
...Will you be my guardian!?

{MEPHIS}
{SETH}.
...Take {WARRICK} to the
{ARMOR TOWER}.
\p{MEPHIS}
{ASTARTE} too must sense that
I have left my seal.
\p{MEPHIS}
Get the armor to {WARRICK} with
all haste.
